BODY: Job Description: At Bank of America, we are guided by a common purpose to help make financial lives better through the power of every connection. Responsible Growth is how we run our company and how we deliver for our clients, teammates, communities and shareholders every day. One of the keys to driving Responsible Growth is being a great place to work for our teammates around the world. We're devoted to being a diverse and inclusive workplace for everyone. We hire individuals with a broad range of backgrounds and experiences and invest heavily in our teammates and their families by offering competitive benefits to support their physical, emotional, and financial well-being. Bank of America believes both in the importance of working together and offering flexibility to our employees. We use a multi-faceted approach for flexibility, depending on the various roles in our organization. Working at Bank of America will give you a great career with opportunities to learn, grow and make an impact, along with the power to make a difference. Join us! This position is not eligible for sponsorship. Job Description: This job is responsible for supporting analytical work efforts for various projects within a Line of Business or business discipline. Key responsibilities include leveraging databases to acquire client and performance data, transforming extracted data into meaningful insights and trends, and delivering those insights to leaders to make complex business decisions. Job expectations include working with business partners to understand, coordinate, and deliver agreed upon priorities while communicating complex data outputs and delivering the appropriate summary and data required. The Client Quantitative Analyst I would be responsible for supporting Consumer At-Risk Persons (ARP) and/or Consumer and Small Business Anti-Money Laundering (AML) compliance within Client Protection. The analyst will lead data-driven efforts to improve client experience and protect clients, as well as the bank, from fraudulent behavior. Ideal candidates will understand customer, product, and time-series (i.e., workflow) data; will be able to "translate" complex business problems into analytics projects; and will be able to provide actionable intelligence to various levels of management, while driving a culture of compliance and operational excellence. Specific duties for this position include, but are not limited to:  Deploy business intelligence and reporting solutions to support Consumer and Small Business AML & ARP strategy and/or investigations  Research and develop analytical methods designed to improve the client protection program process  Deploy analytical methods as production monitoring processes with emphasis on ongoing performance measurement and optimization, as well as comprehensive process documentation  Demonstrate influence through clear and crisp presentation of analytical results and recommendations to senior management  Provide routine and ad hoc reporting, measurement & monitoring of information  Prepare compelling dashboards for management and business partners  See the "story" in data, and clearly and appropriately summarize to audiences including audit and regulatory bodies  Build strong partnerships and collaborate effectively with business, risk, and technology partners Responsibilities: Supports the extraction of data using a variety of a programming languages, such as SQL, SAS, Python, or Spark/Scala, and applies knowledge of relational and non-relational database systems housed on both on-premise and off-premise (hybrid) platforms Connects provisioned data across multiple sources and performs necessary transformations utilizing both technical, business, and process knowledge to transform data into meaningful values and insights Performs quantitative techniques and analysis on customer, transaction, and performance data with the guidance from other analysts and supervisors, based on questions provided by business partners, and provides actionable insights for business partners to make informed decisions. Follows requirements developed by other analysts and supervisors to perform required research, analytics, and exploration on appropriate and accurate data sources to provide appropriate deliverables Communicates complex subjects in a simple and engaging manner to non-technical and technical business partners using software such as Power Point, Word, Excel, and Tableau Assists with conducting quality comparison checks on analysis output and escalates data inconsistencies, gaps, or issues to leadership Follows quality workflow process and documentation requirements to adhere to standards and provide business continuity Skills: Business Analytics Data Mining Data and Trend Analysis Analytical Thinking Business Intelligence Data Quality Management Data Visualization Application Development Business Acumen Continuous Improvement Innovative Thinking Quality Assurance This position is not eligible for sponsorship. Required Qualifications:  3+ years of technology, technology internal control, audit risk or compliance experience for a large and complex organization  Understanding of analytic, visualization, reporting, & query software. Experience building & publishing Tableau dashboards.  Project management experience coordinating processes, procedures, and large technology implementations in partnership with stakeholders.  Understanding of relational database environments and distributed file systems as well as programming experience (i.e. SAS, SQL, Hadoop)  Strong Microsoft Office skills  Ability to interact and influence across all levels of the organization  Excellent verbal, written, and interpersonal communication skills  Ability to document complex processes to improve business continuity, and maintain audit and regulatory credibility  Highly motivated, proactive and a self-starter; strong sense of ownership & ability to create and execute plans without daily oversight  Ability to communicate complex ideas in a clear and concise manner  Ability to connect the dots, and a love of problem-solving  Participation in cross-functional teams and ability to work effectively in a geographically dispersed team Desired Qualifications:  Masters' and/or Bachelor's  Knowledge of financial and banking products, policies, operations and applicable procedures  Experience supporting highly regulated initiatives in large, complex financial institutions  Experience using or administering a SharePoint site  Experience using Alteryx Shift: 1st shift (United States of America) Hours Per Week: 40

BODY:
Senior Analyst - Data Analytics and ing
Full Time
Minnetonka, MN, US
5 days ago
Requisition ID: 1076



JOB SUMMARY



Carlson, Inc. and its affiliated entities, Carlson Holdings, Inc. and the Tonkawa family office, is seeking a full time Senior Analyst - Data Analytics and ing to independently provide analytical support across the different functions of our business. This includes developing and owning models that provide key business and financial projections, helping different groups structure and analyze data relevant for their areas, and building standardized reports to enable automated access to key information and metrics. This position will interface with business clients, providing relevant analytical information and insights and helping them answer critical questions.




The successful candidate will be an inquisitive self-starter, have a growth mindset with an emphasis on continuous improvement, excellent collaboration skills, and a passion for data systems, analytics and reporting.




At Carlson, we believe every voice matters and aim to create a workplace w team members feel wee. We prioritize diversity of thought, experience, and background and aremitted to creating a more inclusive future, both inside ourpany and in ourmunities.




Our office is located in the Carlson towers in Minnetonka, MN and features many amenities including an onsite caf and fitness center. We offer a hybrid work environment (requiring three in office days per week),petitivepensation, and aprehensive benefits package.



KEY RESPONSIBILITIES



Develop and own business models to provide short, medium, and long-term projections, integrating operating revenues, investment returns, and expenses
Conduct sensitivity / scenario analyses to provide insight into potential risks and opportunities
Develop presentation materials tomunicate key findings to staff, clients, Boards, andmittees
 various functional groups structure and analyze data to clarify results, highlight trends, identify issues, and answer questions
Use Power BI and other tools to build standardized reports
Perform ad hoc analysis and projects as requested



QUALIFICATIONS



Bachelor's degree in business, data analytics, or technical area; MBA preferred
Minimum of 2-4 years related experience. A relevant master's degree or professional certification (e.g., CPA or CFA) with less experience may also be acceptable
Advanced knowledge of modeling, data analysis, and data structures
Experience with different analytical and reporting packages (e.g., Power BI) and database programs (e.g., SQL) required
Some familiarity with accounting methods, taxes, and investments
Strong attention to detail and accuracy along with strong analytical, time management, and problem-solving skills
Ability to multi-task, be adaptable to change, and work both independently and as part of a team
Strong written and verbal businessmunication skills
Professionalism, confidentiality, and discretion is of utmost importance
Proficiency in MS Office products (Excel, Word, PowerPoint, Outlook) is required

Acumed LLC

Come join a team where People make the difference! As a part of Marmon Holdings, Inc., a highly decentralized organization, we rely heavily on people with the aptitude, attitude, and entrepreneurial spirit to drive our success, and we're committed to attracting and retaining top talent.

Job Scope

This role involves analyzing complex data to uncover trends, identify opportunities, and support strategic decisions. The ideal candidate has strong analytical skills, advanced data techniques proficiency, and effective communication. Responsibilities include ad-hoc analyses, predictive modeling, and data-driven insights for business growth and efficiency.

The Senior Analyst/Data Scientist handles tasks like trend analysis, regression planning, forecasting, and cost analysis. They must be a self-starter, organized, detail-oriented, and able to present findings, with regular interaction with senior leadership.

Duties/Responsibilities

Data Analysis: Identify trends and insights from complex data sets, providing actionable recommendations.
Predictive Modeling: Develop, test, and deploy models to forecast performance, identify risks, and uncover opportunities.
Ad-Hoc Reporting: Perform analyses to answer specific business questions and support decision-making.
Dashboard Development: Create and maintain interactive dashboards and reports using Power BI.
Data Management: Collect, clean, and organize data from various sources for accurate analysis; skilled in SQL querying and modeling.
Collaboration: Support Sales, Marketing, Finance, and Operations teams with analytical needs.
Communication: Present data analyses and findings clearly to stakeholders and upper management.
Continuous Improvement: Stay updated on trends and technologies to enhance analytical capabilities.
Project Management: Manage multiple projects to deliver high-quality analyses on time.

Qualifications

Education: Bachelor's degree in Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, Mathematics, Economics, or related field; advanced degree preferred.
Technical Skills: Proficiency in Python, R, SQL, Alteryx, Power BI, Tableau; experience with Azure ML, TensorFlow, scikit-learn is a plus.
Experience: 3+ years in data analysis or data science.
Analytical Skills: Strong problem-solving and ability to interpret complex data for actionable insights.
Communication Skills: Excellent verbal and written skills, able to present complex information clearly to upper management.
Attention to Detail: High accuracy in data analysis and reporting.
Business Acumen: Understanding business operations and relating analytical findings to business contexts.
Project Management: Manage multiple tasks and projects effectively.
Team Collaboration: Strong interpersonal skills for working with cross-functional teams.

Target Compensation: $126,680.90 - $154,832.21

Benefits: Medical, Dental and Vision insurance, 401k matching, + more.

Following receipt of a conditional offer of employment, candidates will be required to complete additional job-related screening processes as permitted or required by applicable law.

We are an equal opportunity employer, and all applicants will be considered for employment without attention to their membership in any protected class. If you require any reasonable accommodation to complete your application or any part of the recruiting process, please email your request to careers@marmon.com, and please be sure to include the title and the location of the position for which you are applying.

About Us

With more than 100 autonomous manufacturing and service businesses, Marmon Holdings, Inc. may be the biggest company you've never heard of.Part of Berkshire Hathaway Inc., Marmon is a global industrial organization comprising 11 diverse groups with 20,000-plus employees and $10 billion in annual revenue. 

As leaders in every industry we serve, Marmon companies have earned a great degree of independence. And our people thrive on an entrepreneurial spirit. At the same time, our group structure gives every Marmon company access to the expertise of other Marmon companies serving the same or related markets and customers - all with the support of the entire Marmon organization.

Working together, we become something more than the sum of our parts. We become the most reliable solution provider for a broad range of industries and customers worldwide.

In every case, Marmon's success is due to our people. People with talent, drive and high ethical standards. People who are following their passions and building their careers across Marmon.

Want to learn and perfect your craft? Want to sharpen your skills while helping to solve challenges for our customers and our world? Looking for a chance to grow within - or perhaps outside - your field? Find a Marmon company that matches your passion. And see what you can do with the support of a team that values your contribution.

We advise, design, implement, and deploy innovative and technology enabled solutions focused on "heart of the business" issues in specific sectors including Health Care & Life Sciences, Digital Banking & Payments, Investment & Wealth Management, Insurance, Telecom, Media and Energy & Resources. Our OTT team brings clients the knowledge of industry leaders who understand the relevant processes and technologies for their industry-and apply them with a process and mindset that tailors transformational change to their specific organization. Who we serve Deloitte's Power, Utilities & Renewables practice is at the forefront of top trends and issues facing the ever-evolving power, utilities and renewable energy landscape. Building on more than 175 years of service, our US Power, Utilities & Renewables practice helps clients with some of their most complex challenges as they look to accelerate digital transformation, ignite technological innovation, and navigate more sustainable solutions for energy generation. Work You'll Do As a Manager, you will lead and deliver small engagements, or components of large, complex engagements leadership for Enterprise Asset Management (EAM) implementation and integration projects that identify, design and implement creative business and technology solutions for Power, Utilities & Renewables clients. Using a combination of direct management and hands-on delivery, you will craft solutions for clients, guide and oversee the quality of your team's deliverables and recommendations and manage day-to-day stakeholder relationships. Managers will contribute to Deloitte's thought leadership, play a significant role in business development activities, and own responsibility for the development of junior staff. Successful candidates will accomplish these objectives by: Managing deliverables for utility EAM implementation and integration projects including architectural specifications, use case development, requirements gathering, risk assessment, design specification, test plans, test cases and project financials. Overseeing the quality of deliverables through effectively leading and mentoring teams , leveraging cross-geography insights and delivery professionals and managing client relationships to ensure exceptional performance Leading functional and technical workshops, based on client needs Developing and fostering relationships with clients and establishing credibility a trusted advisor to bring utility EAM domain expertise to a variety of projects. Leveraging deep industry knowledge, insights, trends, and proven approaches to help clients confirm priorities and develop strategies to drive value to the business and customer experience. Participating in the development and presentation of proposals for business development activities Communicating complex ideas effectively, both verbally and in writing, through tools like Microsoft PowerPoint and Microsoft Word Leveraging strong problem solving, critical thinking and trouble shooting skills and demonstrating an ability to exercise mature judge ment. Required Qualifications Bachelor's degree 6 + years' experience working with Utilities clients or experience working with in the Utilities sector 6 + years' experience in an Asset Management, Asset Performance Management, or Work Management capacity within the gas and electric utility industry Experience implementing EAM solutions such as Maximo, IFS/Hexagon Knowledge of database model and service-oriented architecture concepts Knowledge of software programming languages such as Python, Model Builder, FME Workbench, JavaScript, C++ Business process automation experience Proficiency with Microsoft PowerPoint, Microsoft Word and Microsoft Excel Ability to travel 50%, on average, based on the work you do and the clients and industries/sectors you serve Limited immigration sponsorship may be available Preferred Skills Advanced Degree Knowledge of EAM, GIS and OMS enterprise architectures and web applications Consulting experience Experience with Microsoft SharePoint, Microsoft OneNote, Microsoft OneDrive and Microsoft Teams The wage range for this role takes into account the wide range of factors that are considered in making compensation decisions including but not limited to skill sets; experience and training; licensure and certifications; and other business and organizational needs. The disclosed range estimate has not been adjusted for the applicable geographic differential associated with the location at which the position may be filled. At Deloitte, it is not typical for an individual to be hired at or near the top of the range for their role and compensation decisions are dependent on the facts and circumstances of each case. A reasonable estimate of the current range is $144,600 to $241,000. You may also be eligible to participate in a discretionary annual incentive program, subject to the rules governing the program, whereby an award, if any, depends on various factors, including, without limitation, individual and organizational performance. BODY: Oracle HCM Cloud Implementation Specialist - Core HR Module Deloitte - 3.9 Lansing, MI Job Details Full-time Estimated: $131K - $166K a year 7 hours ago Qualifications 7 years Oracle Bachelor's degree Human resources Oracle HCM Big 4 Full Job Description Are you interested in working in a dynamic environment that offers opportunities for professional growth and new responsibilities? Are you interested in helping clients drive alignment with their business, improve organizational and human resource performance and establish a culture focused on adding business value? That is what the new generation of human resource transformation is all about. If you are seeking a role that offers you the opportunity to advise Government and Public Services (GPS) clients through critical and complex issues, while allowing you to develop personally and professionally, consider a career in Deloitte's Human Capital practice. Recruiting for this role ends on June 30 th , 2024. Work you'll do As a Functional Oracle HCM Core HR Specialist on our Human Capital team, you will: Assist with tasks such as: system strategy, gathering and documenting business requirements, leading fit-gap analysis, as-is and to-be business process designs, prototype demonstration, functional configuration, testing, and client user training as it relates to Oracle HCM Cloud Core HR Perform project tasks independently and lead workstreams, directing the efforts of others Participate in and lead the development of deliverable content that meets the needs of the client and contract Review deliverables for accuracy and quality Use your prior experience to anticipate client needs and formulate solutions to client issues The team Deloitte's Government and Public Services (GPS) practice - our people, ideas, technology and outcomes-is designed for impact. Serving federal, state, & local government clients as well as public higher education institutions, our team of over 15,000+ professionals brings fresh perspective to help clients anticipate disruption, reimagine the possible, and fulfill their mission promise. The HR Transformation offering (HRT) transforms the way HR enables the business and the workforce. In this world of disruption, we believe that HR has an opportunity to take the lead and own enterprise-wide issues for the organization. From the creation of HR strategy using our leading Oracle-enabled HR Transformation labs, the application of design thinking that allows HR to challenge how work gets done today, to navigating the ever-evolving HR technology landscape to determine the right digital solutions to enable transformation, our HR Transformation practice is focused on helping HR take the lead. Qualifications Required: 7 years of consulting or industry experience delivering Oracle HCM Cloud solutions Experience as a functional lead on at least 1 full life-cycle implementation of the Core HR module for Oracle HCM Cloud Must be legally authorized to work in the United States without the need for employer sponsorship, now or at any time in the future Ability to travel up to 25-50%, on average, based on the work you do and the clients and industries/sectors you serve Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience Preferred: Big 4 consulting experience Oracle Core HR Cloud Certified Implementation Specialist The wage range for this role takes into account the wide range of factors that are considered in making compensation decisions including but not limited to skill sets; experience and training; licensure and certifications; and other business and organizational needs. The disclosed range estimate has not been adjusted for the applicable geographic differential associated with the location at which the position may be filled. At Deloitte, it is not typical for an individual to be hired at or near the top of the range for their role and compensation decisions are dependent on the facts and circumstances of each case. A reasonable estimate of the current range is $125,000 to $208,000. You may also be eligible to participate in a discretionary annual incentive program, subject to the rules governing the program, whereby an award, if any, depends on various factors, including, without limitation, individual and organizational performance. - Experience working productively in remote model

TITLE_RAW: Workforce Software Technical Subject Matter Expert (SME)
BODY:
V2Soft (www.v2soft.com) is a global company, headquartered out of Bloomfield Hills, Michigan, with locations in Mexico, Italy, India, China, and Germany. At V2Soft, our mission is to provide high-performance technology solutions to solve real business problems. We become our customer's true partners, enabling both parties to enjoy success. We are committed to promoting diversity in the workplace and believe it has a positive effect on our company and the customers we serve.

The primary role for this resource will be to act as a WFS technical/functional subject matter expert. The project team will rely on your expertise to validate the recommendations made by our IP and to challenge them when appropriate. Note: Disregard the related application for this RSO, it is a new application that will replace the CATS (Hourly Timekeeping) application.

Project Description: Our current hourly timekeeping application (CATS) will be replaced with a cloud based SaaS product called SAP/Workforce Software. This RSO is to identify a technical SME with a thorough understanding of the tools provided with the Workforce Software solution and prior experience implementing the WFS solution for a large, complex corporation.

Project Timing & Phases:

Project Start: May 1, 2024
Project End: Oct 31, 2026

Mandatory skills:

Experience with implementing Workforce Software for a large North American company.
Experience with configuring Workforce Software to meet business requirements that vary from what is delivered out of the box.
Experience with the technical tools provided with Workforce Software (e.g. API's, SFTP, Admin Tool, SAP Crystal Reports, SAP Business Objects, etc.)
Experience managing an external vendor to ensure deliverables are provided in a timely manner and meet our business & quality expectations.
Excellent English speaking/writing skills.
Critical thinking, communication and meeting facilitation skills.

Preferred skills

Functional experience with the Workforce Software Time, Attendance & Scheduling modules or experience with another Workforce Management/Timekeeping application.
Experience implementing a leading workforce management application (WFS, UKG, Ceridian, Infor, etc.)
SAP Business Objects platform experience (Crystal, BO Ad Hoc, BO Analytics)
Experience with Change Management & Web Based Training deliverables
Understanding of testing methodology, detail deliverables and ability to play a functional role in the strategy.

V2Soft is an Equal Opportunity Employer ( EOE). - to view all of our open opportunities and to learn more about our benefits.

Job Description
Support Center Analyst
ID 2024-2423
Job Locations	US	Category	Information Technology	Type	Regular Full-Time
Overview

DecisionPoint is seeking a Support Center Analyst as a full-time position to provide end-user support to the Department of Interior, Bureau of Land Management (BLM) Information Technology Operation Support Services. This role is largely responsible for providing operational support services to the organization. We are looking to fill a need to have a highly competent and highly motivated individual in this role.

This position is 100% remote

Duties & Responsibilities
Remote computer support
Owning, tracking and resolving Information Technology (IT) incidents and requests
Fulfilling requests and resolving incidents within SLAs on a daily basis to ensure service-related issues are identified and resolved within established SLAs
Responding to alerts and escalations and working with both user and IT support groups to come up with strategic solutions to recurring problems
Providing Tier I and Tier II onsite and remote (desktop level) support and basic network troubleshooting support.
Providing knowledgeable support for IT incidents by utilizing the Tier 1 Knowledge Base, Knowledge Centered Support (KCS) principles, the Information Technology Infrastructure Library (ITIL), and Subject Matter Experts (SME) along with troubleshooting techniques to provide the appropriate actions for service request resolution. Following Total Contact Ownership methodology.
Placing/Tracking trouble calls to other service providers.
Creating, modifying, or deactivating user accounts.
Developing and maintaining operational & knowledge management documentation in the Help Desk Tier 1 document management system.
Responding to all assigned calls and messages in order of urgency
Following Total Contact Ownership methodology.

Qualifications
High School Diploma
A minimum 1 years of experience
Must be able to evaluate approved security product capabilities and develop solutions
Ability to obtain a Public Trust

**Salary range is $40,000 - $45,000 annually**

Enterprise Data and Analytics Lead
Enterprise Data and Analytics Lead
Fairfax, VA

Posted 1 day ago

Job Description

The Enterprise Data and Analytics Lead is a new senior management role on the Quality team to optimize data and analytics to improve business processes, decisions, and outcomes. We are looking for a candidate with a passion for data and analytics along with industry knowledge for implementing data governance in a large organization. They must have experience implementing a data governance program for a medium to large organization.

Responsibilities Include:

Provide hands on practical experience to design, implement, and support both the technical and managerial aspects for enterprise data and analytics solutions.
Recommend the proper data governance framework and tools for our organization.
Lead our data governance council to recommend, develop, implement, and enforce policies and procedures at the data level concerning stewardship, classification, metadata management, discovery, quality, access, access controls, lifecycle management, and risk management.
Recommends and measures data and analytics deliverables to improve efficiency, user adoption and quality.
Engineer and produce KPIs and metrics that demonstrate business effectiveness in a variety of areas. Builds ad hoc and regular metrics on key performance measures.
Leads the development, testing and delivery of advanced dashboards, visualizations, and reports in Power BI.
Develops and maintains central inventory of data fields in our organization and associated data movement requirements.
s expertise with cross functional departments on data tools and techniques and practices in telling a concise story on data analytic deliverables. May present conclusions and recommendations to Senior Management.
Employ agile development operations to ensure successful achievement of projects and initiatives.
Ensure all activities comply with corporate and Federal Government regulatory requirements.

Qualifications:

Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, a related technical discipline, or equivalent relevant experience.
8+ years of overall work experience in designing, developing, and delivering Enterprise solutions.
4+ years of experience providing data solutions for corporate Enterprise systems (HRIS, ATS, CRM, ERP, et al).
Experience with implementing data governance at a large or mid-size organization.

Candidate capabilities that will lead to success in this role:

Excite others with your passion to improve all aspects of data in our organization through governance and analytics.
Create achievable project plans, adhere to timeline of project deliverables, and secure acceptance and approval of deliverables from stakeholders.
Exude a positive attitude while leading, managing and nurturing a small highly skill technical team.
Guide the production of stunning and easy-to-consume data analytics for executive management and stakeholders.
Employ methodologies and best practices for decomposing KPIs and metrics requests from executives and stakeholders into functional specifications and reusable components from Enterprise systems.
Leverage advanced skills with Microsoft Power BI, Data Studio, DAX, SQL, stored procedures and data modeling.
Resilient by working with minimal direction and guidance in delivering results in a fast-paced work environment.
Effectively collaborate across all levels of management and technical staff within our organization.
Demonstrate strong business acumen.
Excel at written and verbal communications.

BODY:
About Lumen

Lumen connects the world. We are igniting business growth by connecting people, data and applications - quickly, securely, and effortlessly. Together, we are building a culture and company from the people up - committed to teamwork, trust and transparency. People power progress.

Lumen's commitment to workplace inclusion and employee support shines bright. We've made the Newsweek 2024 Greatest Workplaces for Diversity list and achieved a perfect score of 100 on the Human Rights Campaign Corporate Equality Index (CEI) for the fifth consecutive year. Plus, we're the top employer in the communications and telecom industry, ranking 12th overall across all industries in The American Opportunity Index.

We're looking for top-tier talent and offer the flexibility you need to thrive and deliver lasting impact. Join us as we digitally connect the world and shape the future.

The Role

We are looking for a Principal Architect to join our Product Team. You will be responsible for defining and driving the technical vision, strategy, and architecture for our products as they relate to the various segments and customers. You will work closely with product managers and other stakeholders to deliver scalable, secure, and high-performance solutions that meet the needs of our customers and partners.

The Main Responsibilities

Define and communicate the technical vision, strategy, and architecture for the Wholesale product portfolio.

Analyze potential opportunities and emerging technologies to formulate the set of scope from a business perspective that a product project needs.

Evaluate technology and innovation opportunities for the Wholesale segment.

Collaborate with product managers to articulate Wholesale customer needs and feedback on the Lumen product portfolio.

Ensure alignment and integration of the Wholesale product architecture with the enterprise architecture and other product domains.

Evaluate and recommend new and emerging technologies, tools, and platforms that can enhance the Wholesale product capabilities and performance.

Continuously evaluate the market trends and needs to propose solutions best suited for Wholesale customers.

Provide customer feedback to other architects and product managers in the team and across the organization.

Drive innovation and continuous improvement in the Wholesale product domain.

What We Look For in a Candidate

Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.

10+ years of experience in software engineering, architecture, and design.

5+ years of experience in leading and managing complex and large-scale software projects and teams.

Expertise in cloud technologies, microservices, APIs, and DevOps.

Experience in designing and developing solutions for the Wholesale segment of the technology and telecommunications industry.

Experience in evaluating emerging technology and understanding how it applies to Wholesale customers.

Strong knowledge of the Wholesale business processes, products, and services.

Excellent communication, collaboration, and leadership skills.

Compensation

The starting salary for this role differs based on the employee's primary work location. Employees typically do not start at the top of the range, though compensation depends on each individual's qualifications.

Location Based Pay Ranges

$128,310 - $171,080 in these states: AR ID KY LA ME MS NE SC SD

$135,060 - $180,080 in these states: AL AZ FL GA IA IN KS MO MT ND NM OH OK PA TN UT VT WI WV WY

$141,820 - $189,090 in these states: CO HI MI MN NC NH NV OR RI

$148,570 - $198,090 in these states: AK CA CT DC DE IL MA MD NJ NY TX VA WA

As with the pay range variety that's based on the region of a country, specific offers are determined by various factors such as experience, education, skills, certifications and other business needs.

BODY:
Lead SAP EWM Functional Consultant
HTC Global Services wants you. Come build new things with us and advance your career. At HTC Global you'll collaborate with experts. You'll join successful teams contributing to our clients' success. You'll work side by side with our clients and have long-term opportunities to advance your career with the latest emerging technologies.
At HTC Global Services our consultants have access to a comprehensive benefits package. Benefits can include Paid-Time-Off, Paid Holidays, 401K matching, Life and Accidental Death Insurance, Short & Long Term Disability Insurance, and a variety of other perks.
Position Description:
We are seeking a skilled SAP EWM Functional Consultant with expertise in design and implementing SAP EWM solutions. Assignments include analyzing business processes, configuring EWM modules, providing end-user support, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to optimize warehouse operations. Strong understanding of logistics, supply chain, and SAP EWM is essential. Description for Candidates: Design, build and configure SAP EWM to meet business processes and business requirements. Complete end-to-end implementations of SAP EWM in automotive warehouses/manufacturing facilities. Interact with customers to define business processes, write and validate functional specifications, and deliver complex solutions. Ensure timely, cost-effective and successful SAP EWM implementations. Provide end-user training in advance of implementations to ensure plant readiness, as well as on-site hyper care support in care of all NA team implementations.
Skills Required:
Gather, analyze and understand business requirements to successfully design and implement SAP EWM solutions.
Configure and customize SAP EWM modules based on customer specifications, ensuring alignment with industry best practices.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate SAP EWM with external systems, ensuring seamless data flow.
Provide expert guidance on EWM functionality, offering recommendations for process improvements and optimizations.
Conduct workshops and training sessions for end-users, empowering them to effectively utilize SAP EWM features and functionalities.
Participate in the full project lifecycle, from fit-gap analysis to configuration, documentation, training, deployment, and hyper-care support.
Troubleshoot and resolve SAP EWM issues, working closely with technical teams to address any production related challenges.
Collaborate with stakeholders to gather and document functional requirements, ensuring a comprehensive understanding of business needs.
Provide ongoing support and maintenance.
Experience Required:
2 End-to-end implementations of SAP EWM as a core consultant.
6 years of experience configuring SAP EWM.
5 years of experience documenting warehouse/business processes and best practices.
2 years of experience using project tracking tools such as Jira or Rally.
4 years of experience collaborating with developers and service teams to determine and implement the best solution.
2 years of experience working knowledge with other SAP modules: SAP MM, PP or SD.
4 years of experience delivering projects within agile framework.
Education Required:
Bachelors in technology, computer science, information systems or a related field.

This opportunity resides with Live, Virtual, Constructive Solutions, a business group within HII's Mission Technologies division. As a trusted partner to our military customers, we design, develop and operate systems that bring together service members from across the globe to help you train like you fight, because we understand that preparation requires full coordinationnot readiness in piece parts.

Meet HII's Mission Technologies Division
Our team of more than 7,000 professionals worldwide delivers all-domain expertise and advanced technologies in service of mission partners across the globe. Mission Technologies is leading the next evolution of national defense - the data evolution - by accelerating a breadth of national security solutions for government and commercial customers. Our capabilities range from C5ISR, AI and Big Data, cyber operations and synthetic training environments to fleet sustainment, environmental remediation and the largest family of unmanned underwater vehicles in every class. Find the role that's right for you. Apply today. We look forward to meeting you.

To learn more about Mission Technologies, click here for a short video: https://vimeo.com/732533072

Job Description HII Mission Technologies Division is seeking a Security Specialist in support of a large Operations and Maintenance Contract within Mission Technologies.
Positions will be based at global Army training site in Orlando, FL. This position is contingent upon contract award. 
Essential Job Responsibilities  Responsible for establishing and maintaining security protocols for contractor personnel, including clearance verification, building access procedures, badge and CAC issuance.
 This role entails contributing to the Project Staffing Plan to manage cross-utilization while ensuring security integrity, and drafting the Transition-In and Transition-Out Plans, addressing security concerns and coordinating knowledge transfer. Integrates security tasks within the Transition-In IMS and ensure optimal security practices during the transition phases.
 Develops security measures within the QMP to track service metrics, aligning with cost, performance, and schedule goals, and oversees the secure handling of GFI and technical documentation.
 Additionally, they provide security input on property and facility management as part of the TDP, ensuring that security considerations are woven throughout technical direction and project execution.
 They also assist in the proper classification, indexing, and updating of security documents within the Library to maintain confidentiality and integrity, adhering to government regulations.

Minimum Qualifications 3 years relevant experience with Bachelors in related field; 1 year relevant experience with Masters in related field; or High School Diploma or equivalent and 7 years relevant experience.Physical Requirements Minimal mobility, dexterity, or coordination required to operate business machines. Minimal lifting may be required.HII is more than a job - it's an opportunity to build a new future. We offer competitive benefits such as best-in-class medical, dental and vision plan choices; wellness resources; employee assistance programs; Savings Plan Options (401(k)); financial planning tools, life insurance; employee discounts; paid holidays and paid time off; tuition reimbursement; as well as early childhood and post-secondary education scholarships.

Why HII
We build the world's most powerful, survivable naval ships and defense technology solutions that safeguard our seas, sky, land, space and cyber. Our diverse workforce includes skilled tradespeople; artificial intelligence, machine learning (AI/ML) experts; engineers; technologists; scientists; logistics experts; and business administration professionals.

Recognized as one of America's top large company employers, we are a values and ethics driven organization that puts people's safety and well-being first. Regardless of your role or where you serve, at HII, you'll find a supportive and welcoming environment, competitive benefits, and valuable educational and training programs for continual career growth at every stage of your career.

Together we are working to ensure a future where everyone can be free and thrive.
Today's challenges are bigger than ever, and the nation needs the best of us. It's why we're focused on hiring, developing and nurturing our diversity. We believe that diversity among our workforce strengthens the organization, stimulates creativity, promotes the exchange of ideas and enriches the work lives of all our employees.

BODY:
Business Intelligence Analyst
Elite Organization for Elite Professionals
This Jobot Job is hosted by: Justin Rice
Are you a fit? Easy Apply now by clicking the "Apply Now" button and sending us your resume.
Salary: $95,000 - $125,000 per year
A bit about us:
Jobot is working with a Renowned Organization in Fort Worth -- This client is an employer for ELITE Professionals and Treats them Accordingly
Why join us?
So many reasons... Apply and find out.
Job Details
Full Time Opportunity with one of DFW's Premier Organizations. 
Hybrid Schedule -- Very interesting opportunity to work on very cool projects, automations, and creative initiatives. 
*Must have experience in the Financial Services World
Job Details:
We are currently seeking a highly skilled and motivated Business Intelligence Analyst with a strong background in the finance industry to join our dynamic team. The successful candidate will be responsible for transforming data into insights that drive business value. This role involves driving data analytics and reporting across various business functions, using advanced statistical techniques to interpret data and create solutions to business problems. The candidate will work closely with stakeholders to understand their business needs and provide data-driven recommendations. This is a permanent position requiring 3+ years of experience in Business Intelligence using: Excel, Tableau, Scorecards, SSRS, PowerQuery, PowerBI, or equivalent.
Responsibilities:
1. Work closely with stakeholders across the organization to identify business needs and define data requirements.
2. Design, develop, and manage BI solutions, reports, dashboards, and scorecards using Tableau, PowerBI, and SSRS.
3. Utilize PowerQuery to extract, transform, and load data from various sources.
4. Conduct thorough data analysis using advanced statistical techniques to derive insights and provide recommendations.
5. Collaborate with IT teams to ensure data accuracy and consistent reporting by designing and creating optimal processes and procedures.
6. Develop and execute database queries and conduct analyses to support business decision making.
7. Create and maintain documentation including requirements, design, and user manuals.
8. Identify opportunities to improve processes and strategies with technology solutions.
9. Monitor analytics and metrics results, interpreting data and providing recommendations to improve systems and performance.
Qualifications:
1. Bachelor's degree in Business, Finance, Computer Science, or related field. Master's degree is a plus.
2. Minimum of 3 years of experience in a Business Intelligence role in the finance industry.
3. Proficient in BI technologies (Tableau, SSRS, PowerBI, PowerQuery) and database languages (SQL).
4. Strong understanding of data warehousing and ETL techniques.
5. Excellent analytical, problem-solving abilities and attention to detail.
6. Strong communication skills with the ability to present complex data in a simple, understandable way.
7. Ability to work effectively in a team and independently.
8. Proven experience in managing multiple projects concurrently and meeting deadlines.
9. Experience in financial modeling and data-driven financial decision-making is a plus.
10. Ability to understand and find appropriate applications for data and analysis results.
11. High level of proficiency with MS Office Suite, especially Excel.
This is a fantastic opportunity to contribute to a forward-thinking company and help shape its future. If you are a dedicated professional with a passion for data and a desire to drive change through data analysis, we would love to hear from you.
Interested in hearing more? Easy Apply now by clicking the "Apply Now" button.

Career Opportunity:
Job Title:
 SAP FICO Consultant
About 
CodeForce
 360
 Making a career choice is amongst the most critical choices one can make, and it's important for the choice to be calculated with factors such as a company's run of success since its inception and more. But, when you come across a company that has reputation proven with nothing but an illustrious run of success since the day it began, you don't need to think of anything else. That's precisely what some of our employees and prospective employees think when they came across CodeForce 360.
Position Overview
SAP FICO Consultant
Mandatory Skills:
Minimum 7 years of SAP project implementation experience in FICO specializing in COPC, ML, Cost Obj Controlling, and Inventory Accounting.
Experience in Business Process Consulting, problem definition, Architecture/Design/Detailing of Processes.
Strong knowledge of FI/CO integration with other modules such as SD/MM and PP.
Hands-on experience in Design, configuration, and testing of core Financial Accounting (FI) and Managerial Accounting (CO).
At least 3 full cycle FI/CO rollout and ongoing support.
Project experience in SD function, Sales, Billing, Pricing, Materials Management, and Production Planning.
Project experience in Product Costing, BOM cost rollup, Costing run, MTS material Costing, and MTO SO Costing.
Project experience in month-end closing Process for Production order including OH, WIP, variance calculation, result analysis, settlement, etc.
Project experience working with ABAP enhancement/report, BI/Business Objects/WEBi.
Excellent communication and team collaboration skills.
Strongly Preferred Skills:
Knowledge of Data Analytics collaboration with Hadoop and Tableau.
Knowledge of upstream modules like MM, SD, and PP and integration with FI/CO module.

JPC - 188801

Bhushan Reddy

BODY: Oracle HCM Cloud Manager Deloitte - 3.9 Tampa, FL Job Details Full-time Estimated: $145K - $184K a year 10 hours ago Qualifications Microsoft Powerpoint Microsoft Excel 6 years Oracle Sales Talent management Visio Microsoft Office Bachelor's degree Human resources Mentoring SaaS Oracle HCM Leadership Occupational Therapy License Full Job Description The Deloitte Consulting HR Transformation practice is a $600M+ offering, with over 2,000 consulting practitioners, and is part of a $1.5B+ Human Capital Consulting team. Our practice encompasses HR Strategy, technical and functional Cloud HR enabling technologies. What drives you? Is it complex, challenging, possibly global projects? Is it the satisfaction of solving problems and eliminating pain points for your client? Is it working alongside and mentoring the brightest minds in the consulting industry? Is it enhancing your brand in the market by providing amazing client service and establishing career-long client relationships? You will find all of this and more with a career at Deloitte. Working with our Oracle Enabled HR Transformation market offering means you will be working with Oracle's #1 Global HCM Cloud Implementation Partner who had growth of over 45% in 2023. Our commitment to the HCM Cloud product is demonstrated in over 65 successful implementations, including some of the largest Oracle HCM Cloud implementations to date. Recruiting for this role ends on 5/31/2025 Work you'll do As an Oracle HCM Cloud Functional Manager , you will use your knowledge and experience with this premier SaaS tool to help your clients solve the most pressing issues facing their HR function today by: Maintaining a hands-on role to ensure deadlines are met and key deliverables are always accurate Leading your team to deliver superior results for your client Managing all aspects of the project, including monitoring and identifying any project issues early to be able to mitigate any risk for your client Building your reputation within the firm and in the market for the strong Oracle HCM Cloud knowledge you possess Forging strong relationships with both the clients and project teams that will contribute to your growth and development The HRT team At Deloitte Consulting LLP, helping our clients exploit new technologies like employee engagement tools, advanced workforce planning and analytics we empower HR to better support the business and create value. HR organizations now reduce costs and improve operating effectiveness through process improvements, shared services, outsourcing and employee self-service, but that's only part of the story, we help them to drive the value this delivers and help the business achieve its strategic objectives in performance and growth. Learn more about our HR Transformation practice. Qualifications Required is a minimum of 6 years' experience in the following areas: Bachelor's Degree or equivalent years of relevant experience required Hands on experience in multiple Full Life Cycle implementations of the Oracle HCM Cloud (Fusion) product, from planning through design, build, testing and go-live Strong functional knowledge of the system Experience leading a project team, including managing workstream leads to drive their work towards project deadlines and deliverables that are on target and beyond client expectations Experience managing project financials, including monitoring and managing project risks/issues and taking appropriate action to ensure an exceptional project completion for the client Experience mentoring and sharing knowledge with colleagues, to continue to grow and develop your colleagues within the practice Superior communications skills, both verbal and written Experience with Microsoft Office Products such as PowerPoint, Visio, Excel, and Word Ability to travel up to 50%, on average, based on the work you do and the clients and industries/sectors you serve Limited immigration sponsorship may be available Preferred: Oracle HCM Cloud Certification in one or more of the following modules: Core HR, Benefits, Compensation, Payroll, OTL, Absence, ORC, Talent Management. Experience supporting the sales cycle, including but not limited to responding to Requests for Proposals, presenting at Orals, contributing to the creation of Statements of Work Information for applicants with a need for accommodation: https://www2.deloitte.com/us/en/pages/careers/articles/join-deloitte-assistance-for-disabled-applicants.html The wage range for this role takes into account the wide range of factors that are considered in making compensation decisions including but not limited to skill sets; experience and training; licensure and certifications; and other business and organizational needs. The disclosed range estimate has not been adjusted for the applicable geographic differential associated with the location at which the position may be filled. At Deloitte, it is not typical for an individual to be hired at or near the top of the range for their role and compensation decisions are dependent on the facts and circumstances of each case. A reasonable estimate of the current range is $144,600 to $241,000. You may also be eligible to participate in a discretionary annual incentive program, subject to the rules governing the program, whereby an award, if any, depends on various factors, including, without limitation, individual and organizational performance. BODY:
About Lumen

Lumen connects the world. We are igniting business growth by connecting people, data and applications - quickly, securely, and effortlessly. Together, we are building a culture and company from the people up - committed to teamwork, trust and transparency. People power progress.

Lumen's commitment to workplace inclusion and employee support shines bright. We've made the Newsweek 2024 Greatest Workplaces for Diversity list and achieved a perfect score of 100 on the Human Rights Campaign Corporate Equality Index (CEI) for the fifth consecutive year. Plus, we're the top employer in the communications and telecom industry, ranking 12th overall across all industries in The American Opportunity Index.

We're looking for top-tier talent and offer the flexibility you need to thrive and deliver lasting impact. Join us as we digitally connect the world and shape the future.

The Role

We are looking for a Principal Architect to join our Product Team. You will be responsible for defining and driving the technical vision, strategy, and architecture for our products as they relate to the various segments and customers. You will work closely with product managers and other stakeholders to deliver scalable, secure, and high-performance solutions that meet the needs of our customers and partners.

The Main Responsibilities

Define and communicate the technical vision, strategy, and architecture for the Wholesale product portfolio.

Analyze potential opportunities and emerging technologies to formulate the set of scope from a business perspective that a product project needs.

Evaluate technology and innovation opportunities for the Wholesale segment.

Collaborate with product managers to articulate Wholesale customer needs and feedback on the Lumen product portfolio.

Ensure alignment and integration of the Wholesale product architecture with the enterprise architecture and other product domains.

Evaluate and recommend new and emerging technologies, tools, and platforms that can enhance the Wholesale product capabilities and performance.

Continuously evaluate the market trends and needs to propose solutions best suited for Wholesale customers.

Provide customer feedback to other architects and product managers in the team and across the organization.

Drive innovation and continuous improvement in the Wholesale product domain.

What We Look For in a Candidate

Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.

10+ years of experience in software engineering, architecture, and design.

5+ years of experience in leading and managing complex and large-scale software projects and teams.

Expertise in cloud technologies, microservices, APIs, and DevOps.

Experience in designing and developing solutions for the Wholesale segment of the technology and telecommunications industry.

Experience in evaluating emerging technology and understanding how it applies to Wholesale customers.

Strong knowledge of the Wholesale business processes, products, and services.

Excellent communication, collaboration, and leadership skills.

Compensation

The starting salary for this role differs based on the employee's primary work location. Employees typically do not start at the top of the range, though compensation depends on each individual's qualifications.

Location Based Pay Ranges

$128,310 - $171,080 in these states: AR ID KY LA ME MS NE SC SD

$135,060 - $180,080 in these states: AL AZ FL GA IA IN KS MO MT ND NM OH OK PA TN UT VT WI WV WY

$141,820 - $189,090 in these states: CO HI MI MN NC NH NV OR RI

$148,570 - $198,090 in these states: AK CA CT DC DE IL MA MD NJ NY TX VA WA

As with the pay range variety that's based on the region of a country, specific offers are determined by various factors such as experience, education, skills, certifications and other business needs.

Requisition #: 333799

Background Screening

If you are selected for a position, there will be a background screen, which may include checks for criminal records and/or motor vehicle reports and/or drug screening, depending on the position requirements. For more information on these checks, please refer to the Post Offer section of our FAQ page (https://jobs.lumen.com/global/en/faq) . Job-related concerns identified during the background screening may disqualify you from the new position or your current role. Background results will be evaluated on a case-by-case basis.

Pursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.

Equal Employment Opportunities

We are committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all persons regardless of race, color, ancestry, citizenship, national origin, religion, veteran status, disability, genetic characteristic or information, age, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, marital status, family status, pregnancy, or other legally protected status (collectively, protected statuses). We do not tolerate unlawful discrimination in any employment decisions, including recruiting, hiring, compensation, promotion, benefits, discipline, termination, job assignments or training.

Disclaimer

The job responsibilities described above indicate the general nature and level of work performed by employees within this classification. It is not intended to include a comprehensive inventory of all duties and responsibilities for this job. Job duties and responsibilities are subject to change based on evolving business needs and conditions.

To learn more about our bonus structure, you can view additional information here. TITLE_RAW: Senior GTM Specialist Solutions Architect, Microsoft, Enterprise
BODY:
Description

Are you a customer-obsessed builder with a passion for helping customers achieve their full potential? Do you have the business savvy, Microsoft background, and sales skills necessary to help position AWS as the cloud provider of choice for customers? Do you love building new strategic and data-driven businesses? Join the Worldwide Specialist Organization (WWSO) Application Migration and Modernization team as a GTM Specialist Solutions Architect!

The Worldwide Specialist Organization (WWSO) is part of AWS Sales, Marketing, and Global Services (SMGS), which is responsible for driving revenue, adoption, and growth from the largest and fastest growing small- and mid-market accounts to enterprise-level customers including public sector. We work backwards from our customer's most complex and business critical problems to build and execute go-to-market plans that turn AWS ideas into multi-billion-dollar businesses. As part of WWSO, you'll provide expertise across the entire life cycle of an AWS customer initiative, from developing ideas for new services to accelerating the adoption of established businesses. We pride ourselves on thinking big, delivering exceptional results for our customers, and working across AWS as #OneTeam.

As a Senior Solutions Architect for the Microsoft technology stack, you will help customers accelerate their adoption of AWS, and analyzing the technical aspects of building and migrating to AWS. You will also play a key role in working with the AWS Service Teams to help them build the best cloud services on Earth. You will create content and speak publicly about the amazing things that our customers are doing on AWS. Additionally, you will engage with other Solutions Architects and the wider field of technology experts to bring your experience and expertise so they can better support our customers.

Your broad responsibilities will include:

 Design and implement strategic migration plans for Microsoft workloads to AWS, ensuring alignment with client objectives and compliance with regulatory standards.

 Owning the technical engagement and ultimate success around specific implementation projects, as well as defining implementation architectures

 Provide thought leadership in the adoption of .NET applications in the cloud, offering guidance on best practices, scalability, and security.

 Collaborate with cross-functional teams to develop integrated solutions that leverage AWS services to meet the unique needs of the Enterprise and Digital Native Business US customers.

 Lead knowledge-sharing sessions and workshops to educate clients and internal teams on Microsoft migrations and cloud optimization strategies.

 Evaluate emerging technologies and trends in cloud computing and Microsoft ecosystems to inform strategic decisions and innovation efforts.

We are open to hiring candidates to work out of one of the following locations:

Seattle, WA, USA

Basic Qualifications

Bachelor's degree

7+ years design/implementation/consulting experience of distributed applications

5+ years management of technical, customer facing resources

5+ years of Microsoft technical experience

Preferred Qualifications

History of successful technical consulting and/or architecture engagements with large-scale customers or enterprises.

Experience migrating or transforming legacy customer solutions to the cloud.

Familiarity with common enterprise services.

Presentation skills with a high degree of comfort speaking with executives, IT Management, and developers.

Strong written communication skills.

Working knowledge of software development tools and methodologies.

Experience working within software development or Internet-related industries.

AWS Solution Architecture certification or relevant cloud expertise.

Computer Science /relevant degree and/or experience highly desired.

Amazon is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace. Amazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, protected veteran status, disability, age, or other legally protected status. For individuals with disabilities who would like to request an accommodation, please visit https://www.amazon.jobs/en/disability/us.

Our compensation reflects the cost of labor across several US geographic markets. The base pay for this position ranges from $138,200/year in our lowest geographic market up to $239,000/year in our highest geographic market. Pay is based on a number of factors including market location and may vary depending on job-related knowledge, skills, and experience. Amazon is a total compensation company. Dependent on the position offered, equity, sign-on payments, and other forms of compensation may be provided as part of a total compensation package, in addition to a full range of medical, financial, and/or other benefits. For more information, please visit https://www.aboutamazon.com/workplace/employee-benefits. This position will remain posted until filled. Applicants should apply via our internal or external career site.

BODY:
About Lumen

Lumen connects the world. We are igniting business growth by connecting people, data and applications - quickly, securely, and effortlessly. Together, we are building a culture and company from the people up - committed to teamwork, trust and transparency. People power progress.

Lumen's commitment to workplace inclusion and employee support shines bright. We've made the Newsweek 2024 Greatest Workplaces for Diversity list and achieved a perfect score of 100 on the Human Rights Campaign Corporate Equality Index (CEI) for the fifth consecutive year. Plus, we're the top employer in the communications and telecom industry, ranking 12th overall across all industries in The American Opportunity Index.

We're looking for top-tier talent and offer the flexibility you need to thrive and deliver lasting impact. Join us as we digitally connect the world and shape the future.

The Role

We are looking for a Principal Architect to join our Product Team. You will be responsible for defining and driving the technical vision, strategy, and architecture for our products as they relate to the various segments and customers. You will work closely with product managers and other stakeholders to deliver scalable, secure, and high-performance solutions that meet the needs of our customers and partners.

The Main Responsibilities

Define and communicate the technical vision, strategy, and architecture for the Wholesale product portfolio.

Analyze potential opportunities and emerging technologies to formulate the set of scope from a business perspective that a product project needs.

Evaluate technology and innovation opportunities for the Wholesale segment.

Collaborate with product managers to articulate Wholesale customer needs and feedback on the Lumen product portfolio.

Ensure alignment and integration of the Wholesale product architecture with the enterprise architecture and other product domains.

Evaluate and recommend new and emerging technologies, tools, and platforms that can enhance the Wholesale product capabilities and performance.

Continuously evaluate the market trends and needs to propose solutions best suited for Wholesale customers.

Provide customer feedback to other architects and product managers in the team and across the organization.

Drive innovation and continuous improvement in the Wholesale product domain.

What We Look For in a Candidate

Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.

10+ years of experience in software engineering, architecture, and design.

5+ years of experience in leading and managing complex and large-scale software projects and teams.

Expertise in cloud technologies, microservices, APIs, and DevOps.

Experience in designing and developing solutions for the Wholesale segment of the technology and telecommunications industry.

Experience in evaluating emerging technology and understanding how it applies to Wholesale customers.

Strong knowledge of the Wholesale business processes, products, and services.

Excellent communication, collaboration, and leadership skills.

Compensation

The starting salary for this role differs based on the employee's primary work location. Employees typically do not start at the top of the range, though compensation depends on each individual's qualifications.

Location Based Pay Ranges

$128,310 - $171,080 in these states: AR ID KY LA ME MS NE SC SD

$135,060 - $180,080 in these states: AL AZ FL GA IA IN KS MO MT ND NM OH OK PA TN UT VT WI WV WY

$141,820 - $189,090 in these states: CO HI MI MN NC NH NV OR RI

$148,570 - $198,090 in these states: AK CA CT DC DE IL MA MD NJ NY TX VA WA

As with the pay range variety that's based on the region of a country, specific offers are determined by various factors such as experience, education, skills, certifications and other business needs.

Requisition #: 333799

Background Screening

If you are selected for a position, there will be a background screen, which may include checks for criminal records and/or motor vehicle reports and/or drug screening, depending on the position requirements. For more information on these checks, please refer to the Post Offer section of our FAQ page (https://jobs.lumen.com/global/en/faq) . Job-related concerns identified during the background screening may disqualify you from the new position or your current role. Background results will be evaluated on a case-by-case basis.

Pursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, we will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records.

Equal Employment Opportunities

We are committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all persons regardless of race, color, ancestry, citizenship, national origin, religion, veteran status, disability, genetic characteristic or information, age, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, marital status, family status, pregnancy, or other legally protected status (collectively, protected statuses). We do not tolerate unlawful discrimination in any employment decisions, including recruiting, hiring, compensation, promotion, benefits, discipline, termination, job assignments or training.

Disclaimer

The job responsibilities described above indicate the general nature and level of work performed by employees within this classification. It is not intended to include a comprehensive inventory of all duties and responsibilities for this job. Job duties and responsibilities are subject to change based on evolving business needs and conditions.

Salary Range

This information reflects the anticipated base salary range for this position based on current national data. Minimums and maximums may vary based on location. Individual pay is based on skills, experience and other relevant factors.

This position is eligible for either short-term incentives or sales compensation. Director and VP positions also are eligible for long-term incentive. To learn more about our bonus structure, you can view additional information here. (https://jobs.lumen.com/global/en/compensation-information) We're able to answer any additional questions you may have as you move through the selection process.

As part of our comprehensive benefits package, Lumen offers a broad range of Health, Life, Voluntary Lifestyle and other benefits and perks that enhance your physical, mental, emotional and financial wellbeing. You can learn more by clicking here. (https://centurylinkbenefits.com)

BODY:
SAP SD Logistics Consultant
We are seeking a highly skilled SAP SD Logistics Consultant with extensive experience in SAP Logistics Execution (LE) and Warehouse Management (WM). The ideal candidate will have a minimum of 10 years of SAP Logistics experience, including at least two end-to-end implementation projects. This role requires strong expertise in SAP Business Technology Platform (BTP) applications and the ability to work independently as a Subject Matter Expert (SME) in the LE and WM areas.
Key Responsibilities:
Lead and execute end-to-end SAP Logistics Execution implementations.
Design and develop SAP BTP applications to enhance logistics processes.
Provide expert-level guidance and support in LE and WM areas.
Organize and manage project deliverables to meet established schedules.
Collaborate with clients to understand their business processes and design effective SAP solutions.
Communicate effectively with stakeholders and adopt industry best practices.
Qualifications:
Minimum 10 years of experience in SAP Logistics, with a focus on LE and WM.
At least two full lifecycle SAP implementation projects in the logistics area.
Strong proficiency in SAP BTP applications.
Ability to work independently and manage tasks effectively.
Excellent organizational and project management skills.
Strong understanding of business processes from a customer perspective.
Effective communication skills and ability to adopt best practices.

Yes No Job details Here's how the job details align with your . Job type Full-time Location Wilmington, DE 19850 Full job description ESM Business Process Champion - DSNC UK, Macclesfield or SE, Gartuna or US, Wilmington Join us at AstraZeneca as an ESM Business Process Champion in our Operations team. Be part of shaping the future of Operations here at AstraZeneca. Build on our foundations of high performance through agility, responsiveness, reliability and efficiency to deliver our new modalities and complex pipeline to market at speed. Accountabilities: As an ESM Process Champion, you will be responsible for supporting the Digital Supplier Network Collaboration (DSNC) Project, providing subject matter expertise in a variety of Supply Chain, Digital, Data and Analytics areas. You will be part of the core DSNC team responsible for process design and sign off, ensuring that the processes are fit for purpose for AZ and suppliers. Essential experience/skills Extensive Supply Chain knowledge. Extensive Business Process knowledge. Extensive SAP ERP and APO/OMP and other system knowledge. Understanding data and process impact. Change and Project management skills. Significant experience of operating in a global environment. Able to lead strategic projects and initiatives across multiple sites/teams. Strong leadership and influencing skills. Experience working with suppliers / CMOs. Ability to work with complexity and manage ambiguity. Desirable Skills/Experience: A degree or equivalent in Business, Logistics, Sciences or Engineering is preferred, equivalent experience will be considered. SAP ERP and APO/OMP user. Lean experience. Proven project delivery. Demonstrated continuous improvement. Demonstrated process standardisation. Cross-process knowledge. When we put unexpected teams in the same room, we unleash bold thinking with the power to inspire life-changing medicines. In-person working gives us the platform we need to connect, work at pace and challenge perceptions. That's why we work, on average, a minimum of three days per week from the office. But that doesn't mean we're not flexible. We balance the expectation of being in the office while respecting individual flexibility. Join us in our unique and ambitious world. Why AstraZeneca? At AstraZeneca, we are driven by our commitment to deliver accelerated growth and to make people's lives better. We are leading the way in delivering Lean processes that drive greater efficiency and speed. Sustainable practices are at the heart of what we do, ensuring we manage our environmental impact across all our activities and products. We have the ambition to be a performance driven network, combining focused execution with a harmonious team-spirit. If you have the passion and the drive to accelerate growth and make people's lives better, then this is the place for you. Ready to make a positive impact in a team where it means more? !

Our practice encompasses HR Strategy, technical and functional Cloud HR enabling technologies. What drives you? Is it complex, challenging, possibly global projects? Is it the satisfaction of solving problems and eliminating pain points for your client? Is it working alongside and mentoring the brightest minds in the consulting industry? Is it enhancing your brand in the market by providing amazing client service and establishing career-long client relationships? You will find all of this and more with a career at Deloitte. Working with our Oracle Enabled HR Transformation market offering means you will be working with Oracle's #1 Global HCM Cloud Implementation Partner who had growth of over 45% in 2023. Our commitment to the HCM Cloud product is demonstrated in over 65 successful implementations, including some of the largest Oracle HCM Cloud implementations to date. Recruiting for this role ends on 5/31/2025 Work you'll do As an Oracle HCM Cloud Functional Manager , you will use your knowledge and experience with this premier SaaS tool to help your clients solve the most pressing issues facing their HR function today by: Maintaining a hands-on role to ensure deadlines are met and key deliverables are always accurate Leading your team to deliver superior results for your client Managing all aspects of the project, including monitoring and identifying any project issues early to be able to mitigate any risk for your client Building your reputation within the firm and in the market for the strong Oracle HCM Cloud knowledge you possess Forging strong relationships with both the clients and project teams that will contribute to your growth and development The HRT team At Deloitte Consulting LLP, helping our clients exploit new technologies like employee engagement tools, advanced workforce planning and analytics we empower HR to better support the business and create value. HR organizations now reduce costs and improve operating effectiveness through process improvements, shared services, outsourcing and employee self-service, but that's only part of the story, we help them to drive the value this delivers and help the business achieve its strategic objectives in performance and growth. Learn more about our HR Transformation practice. Experience supporting the sales cycle, including but not limited to responding to Requests for Proposals, presenting at Orals, contributing to the creation of Statements of Work Information for applicants with a need for accommodation: https://www2.deloitte.com/us/en/pages/careers/articles/join-deloitte-assistance-for-disabled-applicants.html The wage range for this role takes into account the wide range of factors that are considered in making compensation decisions including but not limited to skill sets; experience and training; licensure and certifications; and other business and organizational needs.
